  • Constructor Details

    • Appointment

      public Appointment(int appointmentID, String title, String description, String location, int contactID, String type, ZonedDateTime startDate, ZonedDateTime endDate, int customerID, int userID)
      Constructor that creates a new appointment with information passed in from either the database or the Add Appointment controller.
      Parameters:
      appointmentID - The ID of the appointment.
      title - The title of the appointment
      description - A description of the appointment's purpose.
      location - The location of the appointment
      contactID - The ID of the contact that is associated with this appointment.
      type - A description of what type of appointment this is.
      startDate - Data for the start of the appointment.
      endDate - Data for the end of the appointment.
      customerID - The ID for the customer that is associated with this appointment.
      userID - The ID for the user that created this appointment.

      public void setAppointmentZoneId(ZoneId zoneId)
      A method that lets the program change the zone ID to the one passed in. This is useful for switching from business ZoneId of Eastern Standard Time to the user's local Zone ID.
      Parameters:
      zoneId - Takes in the zone ID set by the program. This can be used to change to and from Eastern Standard Time.
